Chromatica
Created by Robi Barranco Merino
Copyright (c) 2026

Chromatica is an original methodological and pedagogical system designed for guided color palette construction in branding education.

The conceptual architecture of the system, including:

The phased methodological workflow (Inspiration → Refinement → Application → Review → Export)

The mandatory initial inspiration structure

The comparative archetype and form selection modules

The hybrid evidence-based review integration

The contextual multi-mockup application system

The configurable export framework

was designed and developed by Robi Barranco Merino.

